		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [4.37]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=PraetorFenix&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p><BLOCKQUOTE><b id=fs8>Quote:</b><hr size=1><i>"...then tell him/her 'I will become secondary healer.. i will heal after fight'"</i><hr size=1></BLOCKQUOTE>Agreed, but this only works under certain circumstances.&nbsp;&nbsp;If the cleric is at FM all the time even after fights you can spend your mana on other things.<br><br>The trick to backup healing is not to play cleric until you are out of mana, by the way, it's to save the cleric some mana when he needs it.<br><br>Another method of playing backup healer is to heal when the cleric is out of mana in emergency situations.  This will help ensure your mana goes to where it is needed the most, and isn't wasted when the cleric is full.<br><br>Also, from your post I was unsure whether or not you meant to meditate through battles.  This is a <i>very</i> bad idea, unless you are forced to be puller (when it becomes necessary).  Your melee and tanking abilities are more important to the group than your healing in most circumstances.  In others it is, use your good judgement on this.  Backup healing is more art than science.<br><br><BLOCKQUOTE><b id=fs8>Quote:</b><hr size=1><i>"from level 30 paladin get greater heal.."</i><hr size=1></BLOCKQUOTE>Level 39...<br><br><BLOCKQUOTE><b id=fs8>Quote:</b><hr size=1><i>"Yaulp (increase attack point since your str up.. add some AC), reckless str, holy might (important when fighting caster)"</i><hr size=1></BLOCKQUOTE>Casting Yaulp is a pretty good idea, however I would forego the reckless strength.  Strength has a negligable effect on your damage anyways, and being such a hassle to control this spell is hardly worth the mana spent.<br><br>When you have Holy Might at level 49, don't forget to keep Stun memorized as well!  Having multiple stuns increases your chances of interrupting casters, at level 52 I nearly soloed the Ghoul Arch Magi without him casting a single spell because I had all three stuns up and ready.<br><br><BLOCKQUOTE><b id=fs8>Quote:</b><hr size=1><i>"BUT paladin has better taunt skill.. HEAL"</i><hr size=1></BLOCKQUOTE>And there is a better taunt skill than that, it's called STUN.  Chain casting stuns will almost guarantee that a mob will turn its attention onto you.  Heals are good, but stuns are better.<br><br><BLOCKQUOTE><b id=fs8>Quote:</b><hr size=1><i>"HEAL your enchanter.. heal again.. i guarantee after 1 or 2 heals.. those mobs that been attacking him/her (the enchanter) will come to you"</i><hr size=1></BLOCKQUOTE>In higher level dungeons, your enchanter would already be dead.  Stunning buys the enchanter vital time that is needed, Greater Heal is far too slow to keep a caster alive in the deeper areas of Sebilis, or some areas of the planes.<br><br>[quote]<i>"i usually put lay hand on other side of hotkey"</i>[/quote]Same, I couldn't agree more.<br><br>[quote]<i>"dont get the urge to use it EVERYDAY"</i>[/quote]Again I agree, not much to add here.  If you are caught in a train, make sure you are the last to zone out so you can land lay hands on a team member that may not make it.<br><br>[quote]<i>"Play your role as paladin.. say something like "I will show you hell where you belong %T" or etc etc.. make grouping and the GAME more interesting to YOU and your teamates.."</i>[/quote]And it gets your ass kicked on raids.  I must say, people with macros like this are perhaps some of the most annoying you will meet in higher level encounters.<br><br>Take this one for example:  "CASTING CELE ELIXIR ON %t THE %t!!!!!!!!!!"<br><br>It will show up like this:  "CASTING CELE ELIXIR ON Praetor THE Human!!!!!!!!!"<br><br>And yes, somebody actually said that every 15 seconds in Fear once...  All night.<br><br>[quote]<i>"do NOT solo.."</i>[/quote]I am soloing right now in Lower Guk at 52.  It's actually pretty easy, and decent experience that is comparable to a group.  It just depends on how good your gear is, and how well you play.<br><br>[quote]<i>"go to lord shin ree room and WIPE out entire floor.."</i>[/quote]That's the Shin Lord room that the Ghoulbane drops in.  Lord Shin Ree is an orc in East Commons.</p><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br><b>Praetor</b>, 65th Lord Protector of Ascent (Retired)<br><b>Tiresias</b>, 1st Warrior of Asura (Hopefully)</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >2 Replies</td></tr></table><table width="100%"><tr><td class=mhback>&nbsp;</td><td class=mhback >Thread Subject</a></td><td class=mhback>Started by</a></td><td class=mhback>Replies</a></td><td class=mhback>Last Post</a></td><td class=mhback>Rating</a></td></tr><tr class=mdr>
